cs.CR, cs.SE, cs.SI, cs.PL, cs.DC

The paper focuses on security and privacy issues in Android apps, specifically related to SSL vulnerabilities and information leakage. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CR (Cryptography and Security). Additionally, the paper involves analyzing and testing software, which could fall under cs.SE (Software Engineering) or cs.PL (Programming Languages). The experiments also involve simulating attacks, which could be considered as part of cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) or cs.DC (Distributed, Parallel, and Cluster Computing).
